</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[178,1085,1023,1221]" pageId="9" pageNumber="986">
The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cameron" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[225,349,1023,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Micrillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="986" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suturalis">
<emphasis box="[225,349,1023,1045]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="986">M. suturalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group is characterized by a relatively large, slender, and weakly asymmetric aedeagus with a long series of conspicuous sclerotized spines in the internal sac, and by a broad and shallow posterior excision of the male sternite VIII (
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING V" box="[933,1074,1082,1104]" journalOrPublisher="Linzer Biologische Beitrage" pageId="9" pageNumber="986" pagination="1479 - 1520" part="45" refId="ref9612" refString="ASSING V. (2013): On the Palaearctic and Oriental species of Scymbalium and Micrillus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 45 (2): 1479 - 1520." title="On the Palaearctic and Oriental species of Scymbalium and Micrillus (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae)" type="journal article" year="2013">ASSING 2013</bibRefCitation>
). This group includes two species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cameron" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[529,654,1111,1133]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Micrillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="986" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suturalis">
<emphasis box="[529,654,1111,1133]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="986">M. suturalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species distributed in the south of the Oriental region and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2018" box="[382,472,1140,1162]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Micrillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="986" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kongi">
<emphasis box="[382,472,1140,1162]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="986">M. kongi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a new species from 
<collectingCountry box="[687,791,1140,1162]" name="Cambodia" pageId="9" pageNumber="986">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
described below. In external characters they are similar to species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[669,777,1169,1191]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Micrillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="986" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="badius">
<emphasis box="[669,777,1169,1191]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="986">M. badius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, but distinguished by smaller body size and undilated protarsomeres I-IV.
</paragraph>
